cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel approach to tackle the problem of mode collapse in generative adversarial networks (GANs) by introducing a dual discriminator architecture. The paper also conducts extensive experiments on various datasets to evaluate the performance of the proposed method. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments are conducted on image datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR-10, STL-10, and ImageNet. 

Furthermore, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as GANs are a popular topic in the field of AI and the paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of GANs. 

It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the proposed method involves training neural networks to generate diverse samples. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.GR (Graphics) as the paper deals with generating images using GANs.
